   602вҶ’## Update Check
   604вҶ’Tock automatically checks for updates once a week. When a new version is available, you will see a notification after running commands like `start` or `stop`.
   605вҶ’
   606вҶ’You can disable this check by setting `check_updates: false` in your configuration file or using the environment variable `TOCK_CHECK_UPDATES=false`.
   607вҶ’
   608вҶ’## File Format
   610вҶ’Activities are stored in plaintext format (compatible with Bartib):
   611вҶ’
   612вҶ’```
   613вҶ’  2025-12-10 09:00 - 2025-12-10 11:30 | Project Name | Task description
   614вҶ’  2025-12-10 13:00 | Another Project | Ongoing task
   615вҶ’```
   616вҶ’
   617вҶ’You can edit this file manually with any text editor.
   618вҶ’
   619вҶ’## Shell Completion
   621вҶ’Tock supports shell completion for Bash, Zsh, Fish, and PowerShell. This includes basic command completion and **intelligent suggestions** for:
   622вҶ’
   623вҶ’- **Projects**: Suggests existing project names when using `-p` / `--project`.
   624вҶ’- **Descriptions**: Suggests recent activity descriptions when using `-d` / `--description`.
   625вҶ’  - Suggestions are context-aware: if a project is selected, it only suggests descriptions previously used for that project.
   626вҶ’- **Continue IDs**: Suggests valid activity IDs (with details) for the `tock continue` command.
   627вҶ’
   628вҶ’### Installation
   656вҶ’## Shell Integration
   658вҶ’You can display the current tracked activity directly in your shell prompt.
   659вҶ’
   660вҶ’### Zsh / Oh My Zsh
   679вҶ’### Starship
   692вҶ’### Technology Stack
   698вҶ’### Project Structure
   709вҶ’## Inspiration
   711вҶ’Tock is inspired by and compatible with [Bartib](https://github.com/nikolassv/bartib) - an excellent time tracking tool written in Rust by Nikolas Schmidt-Voigt. It's saved me countless hours and helped me stay organized, so I wanted to create a similar tool in Go with a clean architecture approach and an interactive terminal UI.
   712вҶ’
   713вҶ’## License
   715вҶ’GPL-3.0-or-later

